Findings: Comparison is made with multiple prior studies including the most recent one. There is no evident pneumothorax. Extensive bilateral subcutaneous emphysema is unchanged. Patient has known severe emphysema. Multifocal lung opacities, larger in the left upper lobe, right mid and right lower lungs, are stable. There are no new lung abnormalities or pleural effusions. Tracheostomy tube is in standard position. Right mid thoracic chest tube is in unchanged position. A catheter projecting in the right lower lateral hemithorax is likely outside the patient. Left subclavian catheter tip is in the upper SVC. Cardiomediastinal contours are unchanged.
